nujuwmu AlOaxoci The Mansions of the Moon; (Ṣ, L, Ḳ;) also called nujuwmu AlOanowaMCN; 
(L; [see art. nwC;]) 
called by the former appellation because the moon every night enters (yaOoxucu fiI) one of those mansions: (Ṣ, L:) or the stars which are cast at those [devils] who listen by stealth [to the conversations of the angels]: (L, Ḳ:) but the former explanation is the more correct. (L.)

