AisotN, signifying The podex, or the anus, (Ḳ,) or signifying the former, and sometimes used as meaning the latter, (Ṣ in art. sth,) is with a conjunctive hemzeh, [written QsotN, when not immediately preceded by a quiescence,] and its final radical letter is clided; 
for the original form is satahN; (Mṣb;) 
and it is mentioned in art. sth. (Ḳ.) [It is of the fem. gender.] 
It is said in a prov., applied to him who fails of attaining the object that he seeks, OaxoTaOati Qsotuhu AlHuforapa [His anus missed the hole in the ground]. (Meyd.)

hom.sense:
Os-Ahu, (Ṣ, M, Ḳ,) inf. n. taOosiyapN, (Ṣ, Ḳ,) i. q. Eaz-aAhu [He exhorted him, or enjoined him, to be patient; to take patience; or to take example by, or console himself by the example of, him who had suffered the like affliction]; (Ṣ, M, Ḳ, TA;) saying to him, Wherefore dost thou grieve, or mourn, when such a one is thine example (Uisowatuka) i. e. what has befallen thee befell him, and he was patient; therefore take thou example by him and so be consoled (taOas-i bihi). (TA.) 
You say, Os-Ahu bimuSiybapK i. e. Eaz-aAhu [He exhorted him, or enjoined him, to be patient,, &c., by mentioning an affliction that had befallen another; unless bmSytp be a mistranscription for limuSiybapK on account of an affliction]; 
as also MsAhu↓, with medd. (TA.)

entry.sense:
OuXonaAnN and UiXonaAnN, (Mṣb, Ḳ,) but the former is of higher authority than the latter, (TA,) i. q. HuroDN [Kali, or glasswort]: (Mṣb in the present art.; and Ṣ, A, Mgh, Mṣb, Ḳ, in art. HrD:) [and also potash, which is thence prepared;] a thing, or substance, well known, (Ḳ, TA,) with which clothes and the hands are washed; 
